y of public health.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 7aHISTORY / Modern / 17th Century.2bisacsh  aAttentiveness, Pestilence, Marseille, coast.1 aDemichel, Sébastien, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHengerer, Mark Sven, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2023 Englishz978311131913108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2023z9783111318189oZDB-23-DEG0 cEPUBz97831110262440 cprintz978311102612140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783111026169zOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783111026169zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783111026169/original  a978-3-11-131913-1 EBOOK PACKAGE History 2023 Englishb2023  a978-3-11-131929-2 EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishb2023  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DEGb2023  aZDB-23-DGGb2023  aZDB-23-GOA